<div class="recipe-container">
    <h1>Dal Makhani</h1>

    <div class="recipe-description">
        <p><strong>Dal Makhani</strong> is a rich and creamy North Indian lentil dish made with whole black lentils (urad dal) and kidney beans (rajma), slow-cooked with butter and aromatic spices. It pairs perfectly with naan, roti, or basmati rice.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ingredients">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <div class="ingredient-list">
            <div class="ingredient-item">
                <p><strong>Main Ingredients:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>1 cup Whole black lentils (Urad dal)</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Kidney beans (Rajma)</li>
                    <li>4 cups Water</li>
                    <li>1 medium Onion (finely chopped)</li>
                    <li>2 large Tomatoes (pureed)</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Ginger-garlic paste</li>
                    <li>1/2 cup Fresh cream</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp Butter</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Ghee</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Cumin seeds</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Turmeric powder</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Red chili powder</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Garam masala</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Coriander powder</li>
                    <li>Salt to taste</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp Kasuri methi (Dried fenugreek leaves)</li>
                    <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="ingredient-item">
                <p><strong>For Tempering:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>1 tbsp Butter</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Cumin seeds</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Garlic (finely chopped)</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Kashmiri red chili powder</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cooking-instructions">
        <h2>How to Cook</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Soak the Lentils:</strong> Soak urad dal and rajma overnight in water.</li>
            <li><strong>Cook the Lentils:</strong> Pressure cook with 4 cups of water for 6-7 whistles or until soft.</li>
            <li><strong>Prepare the Base:</strong> In a pan, heat butter and ghee, then add cumin seeds.</li>
            <li><strong>Sauté the Aromatics:</strong> Add onions and ginger-garlic paste. Sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li><strong>Add Spices & Tomato Puree:</strong> Mix in turmeric, chili powder, coriander powder, and pureed tomatoes. Cook until oil separates.</li>
            <li><strong>Combine Lentils & Simmer:</strong> Add the cooked lentils, salt, and some water. Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.</li>
            <li><strong>Add Cream & Kasuri Methi:</strong> Stir in fresh cream and crushed kasuri methi for a rich flavor.</li>
            <li><strong>Final Tempering:</strong> In a small pan, heat butter, add cumin seeds, garlic, and Kashmiri red chili powder. Pour over the dal.</li>
            <li><strong>Garnish & Serve:</strong> Top with fresh coriander leaves and serve hot.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="tips">
        <h2>Tips & Variations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>For extra creaminess, blend a portion of the dal before adding it back.</li>
            <li>Slow-cooking enhances the flavors, so let it simmer longer if possible.</li>
            <li>Use Kashmiri red chili powder for color without too much heat.</li>
            <li>For a smoky flavor, try the "Dhungar method" (charcoal smoking technique).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="serve">
        <h2>Serving Suggestions</h2>
        <p>Serve hot with naan, roti, jeera rice, or plain basmati rice. A drizzle of extra cream on top enhances the richness.</p>
    </div>
</div>
